@VitalikButerin Formal verification for smart contracts has been the white whale of Ethereum security for years.

A high-level language that compiles to Lean would be transformative for DeFi.

The attack surface shrinks dramatically when you can mathematically prove correctness. 🐋

Cetus DLMM has undergone multiple rounds of audits and formal verification, with its security certified by several firms.

@LeafSheepfi is a protocol that helps users actively manage their liquidity on Cetus DLMM to achieve higher returns.

The goal is to generate more trading fees on Cetus DLMM, delivering greater rewards to $xCETUS stakers.
